The White House Office of Science and Technology Policy (OSTP) organized an event called "American Leadership in Emerging Technology" to discuss the importance of emerging technologies in driving American prosperity. The event brought together industry leaders involved in developing, financing, and safeguarding promising new technologies. Three breakout sessions were held to discuss Unmanned Aircraft Systems (UAS), 5th generation wireless systems (5G) and the Internet of Things (IoT), and financial investment in emerging technologies. Key takeaways from the discussions included the need for policies that keep pace with technological innovation and the importance of regulatory frameworks and commercialization pathways. Attendees also had the opportunity to meet with President Trump, Vice President Pence, and other senior Administration officials to discuss the issues raised. Interactive demonstrations were presented to showcase the potential of emerging technologies, including drones, connected devices, and 5G technology.